## Build & Deploy

```bash
npx opennextjs-cloudflare build          # Next.js ŌåÆ Cloudflare worker bundle
npx wrangler deploy .open-next/worker.js # deploy (reads wrangler.jsonc)
```

See "Commit, Push & Deploy" above for the full workflow including git push with SSH key.

After deploying schema changes, run migrations via:
```bash
curl -sk "https://greenbrook-framers.hannes-magnusson.workers.dev/api/setup"
```

## D1 Queries from CLI

```bash
npx wrangler d1 execute framers-v2 --remote --command "SELECT ..."
```
Note: D1 CLI may fail with auth errors from local machine. Use `/api/setup` endpoint or `/api/debug` actions instead.

## Worker Execution Limits

Cloudflare Workers have a ~30s CPU time limit. For long operations (e.g. bulk scraping, backfill):
- Process one item at a time via repeated API calls
- Use the `/api/debug` endpoint with single-item actions
- Never try to loop through many external fetches in a single request
